FBIS3-35103 "drnes034_n_94002" FBIS-NES-94-034 Document Type:Daily Report 18 Feb 1994 LEBANON Report on U.S. Message Denied NC1802133794 Beirut Voice of Lebanon in Arabic 1215 GMT 18 Feb 94 NC1802133794 Beirut Voice of Lebanon Language: Arabic Article Type:BFN [Text] Defense Minister Muhsin Dallul has denied a MENA report citing a responsible source at the U.S. State Department saying that he received a message from Secretary of State Christopher informing him that Israel may carry out a large-scale offensive against the south. Dallul added that U.S. Ambassador Mark Hambley expressed satisfaction with the progress of the Lebanese Army and informed him of the U.S. Congress' approval of the deal to grant Lebanon armored personnel and troop carriers. He added that the deal, which has been on hold, involves between 100 and 150 carriers.
